OL,3,C'I had to tell my dad he had cancer':
OL,4,CSerious failings in deaf healthcare
OL,6,FShe said: "The healthcare providers
OL,7,Frelied on me to do all that
OL,8,Finterpreting. I had to suppress every
OL,9,Femotion to be able to translate, and
OL,10,Fit wasn't just at that moment. It was
OL,11,Fright the way through his treatment up
OL,12,Funtil he died.
OL,14,F"In the process, I forgot to be a
OL,15,Fdaughter, I didn't have the
OL,16,Fopportunity to be a daughter. Cancer
OL,17,Fstole his life, but the failures of
OL,18,Fthe NHS and the lack of access to
OL,19,Finterpreters stole time from us."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/8
