OL,3,C'I had to tell my dad he had cancer':
OL,4,CSerious failings in deaf healthcare
OL,6,F"He was used to not having that access
OL,7,Fand campaigned for improvements, and
OL,8,Funfortunately, they never happened and
OL,9,Fdidn't happen in time for him."
OL,11,FIn Wales, more than 900 people have
OL,12,FBSL as their main language and nearly
OL,13,F600,00 people are deaf and hard of
OL,14,Fhearing.
OL,16,FKate has now joined calls for more to
OL,17,Fbe done to improve the provision of
OL,18,FBSL interpreters across all healthcare
OL,19,Fsettings, to address what are
OL,20,Fdescribed as "serious and widespread
OL,21,Ffailings".
