OL,3,C'I had to tell my dad he had cancer':
OL,4,CSerious failings in deaf healthcare
OL,6,F"She's had to go into hospital on a
OL,7,Fnumber of occasions as an emergency
OL,8,Fpatient, and each time she's not had
OL,9,Faccess to a British Sign Language
OL,10,Finterpreter, so therefore she's
OL,11,Fstruggled to communicate", Martin said.
OL,13,FHe said that without his help or the
OL,14,Fhelp of an interpreter, he worries
OL,15,Fcritical things might be missed.
OL,17,F"I've actually witnessed my wife being
OL,18,Fquestioned by healthcare professionals
OL,19,Fand giving incorrect answers when
OL,20,Fthere's not a British Sign Language
OL,21,Finterpreter present.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/8
