OL,3,C'I had to tell my dad he had cancer':
OL,4,CSerious failings in deaf healthcare
OL,6,F"This could lead to the wrong
OL,7,Finvestigations taking place or a
OL,8,Fmisdiagnosis."
OL,10,FPolly Winn, from the RNID, says these
OL,11,Fconcerns have real-life impacts, and
OL,12,Fit is far too common in Wales.
OL,14,F"It's really hard to overstate the
OL,15,Fimpact this has on deaf people," she
OL,16,Fsaid.
OL,18,F"It is stripping them of their
OL,19,Findependence, privacy, and decency.
